## Configuration — Always Pydantic BaseSettings

```python
# config.py
from pydantic_settings import BaseSettings
from pydantic import Field


class IngestorSettings(BaseSettings):
    alpaca_api_key: str = Field(..., alias="ALPACA_API_KEY")
    alpaca_secret_key: str = Field(..., alias="ALPACA_SECRET_KEY")
    symbols_to_track: list[str] = Field(default=["AAPL", "TSLA", "GOOG"])
    redis_url: str = Field(default="redis://localhost:6379")
    max_price_history: int = Field(default=100)

    model_config = ConfigDict(env_file=".env", populate_by_name=True)
```

Never hardcode credentials or URLs. Never `os.getenv()` in business logic — read from settings object only.

