## FastAPI Patterns

### Lifespan for startup/shutdown (not deprecated `@app.on_event`)
```python
from contextlib import asynccontextmanager
from fastapi import FastAPI


@asynccontextmanager
async def lifespan(app: FastAPI):
    # startup
    redis = await connect_redis(settings.redis_url)
    app.state.redis = redis
    app.state.ingestor = DataIngestor(...)
    asyncio.create_task(app.state.ingestor.start())
    yield
    # shutdown
    await redis.aclose()


app = FastAPI(lifespan=lifespan)
```

### Dependency injection for Redis and settings
```python
from fastapi import Depends

def get_redis(request: Request) -> Redis:
    return request.app.state.redis

@app.get("/health")
async def health(redis: Redis = Depends(get_redis)) -> HealthResponse:
    ...
```

### Response models always typed
```python
class HealthResponse(BaseModel):
    status: Literal["ok", "degraded", "error"]
    redis_status: Literal["connected", "disconnected"]
    tracked_symbols: list[str]
    provider: str

@app.get("/health", response_model=HealthResponse)
async def health() -> HealthResponse:
    ...
```

