## Error Handling Hierarchy

```
Exception (truly unexpected — let it propagate to global handler)
  └── AppError (base for domain errors — catch at service boundary)
        ├── TickValidationError     (bad provider payload)
        ├── InsufficientFundsError  (portfolio can't execute)
        └── RedisUnavailableError   (connectivity issue)
```

```python
# Global FastAPI handler — always register this
@app.exception_handler(Exception)
async def unhandled(request: Request, exc: Exception) -> JSONResponse:
    logger.error("Unhandled exception", exc_info=exc, extra={"path": str(request.url)})
    return JSONResponse(status_code=500, content={"detail": "Internal server error"})
```

