## Math & Indicators — Keep It Stdlib

```python
import statistics

# Use statistics module for simple indicators
mean = statistics.mean(prices)
stdev = statistics.stdev(prices)
z_score = (current_price - mean) / stdev

# Use numpy ONLY if it's already in requirements.txt
# Do NOT add numpy just for one strategy
```

Never add a new dependency just to avoid 5 lines of math.
If numpy is needed (e.g., FFT, matrix ops), add it explicitly to `requirements.txt` with a comment explaining why.

