## Checklist — Every PR / Task

- [ ] All functions and methods have full type hints
- [ ] New domain objects are Pydantic models (not dicts, not dataclasses)
- [ ] No blocking I/O in async functions
- [ ] No credentials or URLs hardcoded — settings object only
- [ ] Errors that are expected failures use `Result[T, E]`, not exceptions
- [ ] Constants are named and typed at module level
- [ ] New FastAPI routes have `response_model` set
- [ ] Structured logging with `extra={}` fields (not f-string soup)
- [ ] Tests exist for the new code (unit tests minimum, integration if Redis is involved)
- [ ] No new dependency added without updating `requirements.txt` and a comment

