## Hard Rules

- ❌ No `print()` in production code — use `logger`
- ❌ No `time.sleep()` — use `asyncio.sleep()`
- ❌ No mutable default arguments `def foo(items=[]):`
- ❌ No bare `except:` — always catch a specific type
- ❌ No `Any` type unless wrapping a truly untyped third-party library, with a comment
- ❌ No business logic in `main.py` — it wires things, it doesn't compute things
- ❌ No cross-service imports — Ingestor and Engine are separate packages
